				\begin{document}$$V_p(q)\sim q^{ - 1/2}$$\end{document}, respectively, implying that the piezoelectric coupling would reach a maximum for the smallest wave vector allowed by a finite-sized NC. The small-q acoustic phonons, with their wavelengths (approximately the NC size) being much longer than the lattice constant, can be described by the elastic continuum theory, and their wave velocity and polarization along a given direction can be obtained by solving the Christoffel equation44.

